rlm-pre-commit-pr [base-branch]

Run pre-commit on every file changed on the current branch
since it forked from `base-branch` (default: main).

Resolves the fork point with `git merge-base --fork-point`,
falling back to a plain `git merge-base` if the reflog has no
fork-point information. Then collects added / copied / modified
/ renamed files via `git diff --name-only --diff-filter=ACMR
<fork>...HEAD` and passes them all to `pre-commit run --files`.

Prints a one-line summary `pre-commit-pr: base=<base>
fork_point=<sha> files=<n>` before invoking pre-commit.

Exits 0 with a "no changed files" message if nothing has
changed vs `base-branch`. Exits 1 if no merge base can be
found.

Aliases: pre-commit-pr, pcpr (and rlm-pcpr)
